01:00:17,489 --> 01:00:20,282
Sometimes, under pressure from the police,

1219
01:00:20,367 --> 01:00:23,285
kids can say a lot of things
to keep themselves out of trouble.

1220
01:00:23,829 --> 01:00:25,287
Get out here, Desmond.

1221
01:00:26,206 --> 01:00:27,123
[stereo turns off]

1222
01:00:27,207 --> 01:00:28,582
My son doesn't lie.

1223
01:00:29,167 --> 01:00:31,418
I want to be able to help
to clear this thing up.

1224
01:00:32,254 --> 01:00:33,087
Sit.

1225
01:00:37,425 --> 01:00:38,634
Talk to the man.

1226
01:00:39,219 --> 01:00:41,804
Um... Hi, Desmond.

1227
01:00:41,888 --> 01:00:45,182
I'm, uh, Wynston Himes.
I'm your councilman in this district.

1228
01:00:46,393 --> 01:00:47,768
I seen your picture.

1229
01:00:48,353 --> 01:00:49,520
Right. Um...

1230
01:00:51,481 --> 01:00:53,232
Can you tell me what happened that night?

1231
01:00:55,443 --> 01:00:56,944
Go on. Tell the man what you told me.

1232
01:00:58,280 --> 01:00:59,488
[sighs]

1233
01:00:59,573 --> 01:01:02,491
Me and my friend Tito was hanging out
at the park.

1234
01:01:02,576 --> 01:01:04,368
Not doing nothing.

1235
01:01:05,453 --> 01:01:07,037
Sitting on this bench.

1236
01:01:07,873 --> 01:01:10,916
And this dude in sweats sit by us,

1237
01:01:11,001 --> 01:01:15,129
and start talking that
he give us money if we let him...

1238
01:01:16,506 --> 01:01:17,339
You know.

1239
01:01:19,134 --> 01:01:20,467
What words did he say?

1240
01:01:21,803 --> 01:01:23,304
Suck us off.

1241
01:01:23,889 --> 01:01:26,473
Then he reached for me,
but he didn't touch me.

1242
01:01:26,558 --> 01:01:28,601
See, don't nobody touch me.

1243
01:01:29,144 --> 01:01:30,144
But he was gonna.

1244
01:01:30,770 --> 01:01:33,272
That's when Tito went off on the man,
pops him in the face,

1245
01:01:33,356 --> 01:01:35,316
one, two, three, and we run off.

1246
01:01:36,067 --> 01:01:36,984
And that's it?

1247
01:01:37,736 --> 01:01:39,820
Then the cops catch us and run us in.

1248
01:01:40,405 --> 01:01:43,699
That's the truth? Not just saying this
to stay out of trouble?

1249
01:01:44,242 --> 01:01:46,869
My son doesn't lie, mister.

1250
01:01:48,121 --> 01:01:50,039
And he ain't going to no family court.

1251
01:01:51,166 --> 01:01:53,667
Well, I'll try and make sure
that doesn't happen.

1252
01:01:54,252 --> 01:01:56,003
Thank you for talking to me.

1253
01:01:56,087 --> 01:01:58,130
Oh, and if any newspaper people
come by, try not to--

1254
01:01:58,215 --> 01:02:01,258
We already talked with a man
from Black Courierthis morning.

1255
01:02:01,343 --> 01:02:02,301
Uh-huh.

1256
01:02:02,385 --> 01:02:06,013
Them faggots always after you
up to the park.

1257
01:02:06,097 --> 01:02:08,098
Be happening all the time, mister.

1258
01:02:08,183 --> 01:02:09,433
Get back in your room, Desmond.

1259
01:02:13,688 --> 01:02:14,688
Thank you.

1260
01:02:18,818 --> 01:02:22,279
His son was third party
in a robbery attempt last night.

1261
01:02:22,364 --> 01:02:25,908
The other two got caught, he got away.
We haven't ID'd him yet.

1262
01:02:26,451 --> 01:02:27,284
Hard evidence?

1263
01:02:27,369 --> 01:02:29,495
I can nail his ass to the wall.

1264
01:02:31,081 --> 01:02:31,914
Look at that.

1265
01:02:32,832 --> 01:02:34,083
My heart rate.

1266
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:35,000
Yeah.

1267
01:02:35,543 --> 01:02:38,921
I croak on this damn thing,
they'll be able to make a printout of it.

1268
01:02:40,340 --> 01:02:42,675
Anyway, I thought you'd be interested.

1269
01:02:43,510 --> 01:02:44,885
I appreciate it, Bill.

1270
01:02:45,637 --> 01:02:48,305
If things turn out right,
we won't forget you.

1271
01:02:58,692 --> 01:03:00,317
We could do it through our own office.

1272
01:03:00,402 --> 01:03:01,360
I can handle it.

1273
01:03:01,444 --> 01:03:03,654
We've got a timetable on this, mayor.

1274
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:05,572
The Japanese want it cleared
by the weekend.

1275
01:03:05,657 --> 01:03:08,200
If the Japanese pull their money out,
we got a real...

1276
01:03:08,827 --> 01:03:10,327
I can handle it.

1277
01:03:11,079 --> 01:03:13,706
Right, it's your turf.

1278
01:03:13,790 --> 01:03:15,457
Rinaldi's practically your brother.

1279
01:03:15,542 --> 01:03:17,960
All you goombahs
are practically brothers, right?

1280
01:03:18,044 --> 01:03:19,628
We just need those buildings cleared.

1281
01:03:19,713 --> 01:03:22,881
-I don't want to hear Parks Department.
-Ben Ianucci, that mamaluke.

1282
01:03:22,966 --> 01:03:24,717
Do you people ever go in that park?

1283
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:27,636
There are no street lights.
It's like the Dark Ages, medieval times.

1284
01:03:27,721 --> 01:03:30,931
-A professor got mugged there last night.
-A supposedly intelligent person.

1285
01:03:31,016 --> 01:03:33,809
I wouldn't go out in that park
in a Sherman tank after dark.

1286
01:03:33,893 --> 01:03:36,020
-Pauly, come inside.
-Like a Charles Bronson movie.

1287
01:03:36,104 --> 01:03:37,896
-Excuse me, ladies.
-There's animals out there.

1288
01:03:37,981 --> 01:03:38,939
Now. Pauly.

1289
01:03:39,024 --> 01:03:40,774
Fiscal crisis. Excuse me.

1290
01:03:42,902 --> 01:03:45,654
-They don't listen.
-They never listen.

1291
01:03:45,739 --> 01:03:47,740
[indistinct chatter]

1292
01:03:55,206 --> 01:03:57,916
Yo, Gus. [whistles]
So, what's the fucking story here?

1293
01:03:58,001 --> 01:03:59,543
You're shut down, Joe.

1294
01:03:59,627 --> 01:04:00,586
For what?

1295
01:04:00,670 --> 01:04:03,505
You got a septic clearance
that isn't up to spec.

1296
01:04:03,590 --> 01:04:05,799
I got a green light on that months ago.

1297
01:04:05,884 --> 01:04:07,343
Yeah, but not on paper.

1298
01:04:08,053 --> 01:04:09,470
You know where it came from.

1299
01:04:09,554 --> 01:04:13,640
I know. Then I suggest you go back
to where it came from, and talk to them.

1300
01:04:13,725 --> 01:04:15,642
What the fuck you think I'm out here for?

1301
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:19,146
Septic clearance, my ass.

1302
01:04:21,483 --> 01:04:22,566
Still on the clock, Joe.

1303
01:04:22,650 --> 01:04:26,236
You call Belcher and get off the clock.
This could take a week.

1304
01:04:26,321 --> 01:04:28,822
Belcher says no breaks from the Local.

1305
01:04:28,907 --> 01:04:30,115
Contract stands.

1306
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:31,825
What the fuck is that?

1307
01:04:31,910 --> 01:04:33,619
Your juice has been cut off, Joe.

1308
01:04:34,537 --> 01:04:37,206
Whatever problems you got downtown,
you clean them up,

1309
01:04:37,290 --> 01:04:38,832
we can cut you some slack.

1310
01:04:38,917 --> 01:04:41,418
Come on. Don't take it personal.

1311
01:04:42,295 --> 01:04:43,670
Yo, Tommy.

1312
01:04:43,755 --> 01:04:45,672
-Joe...
-[Yoyo] Tommy, wait up.

1313
01:04:45,757 --> 01:04:47,007
Man, I'm sorry.

1314
01:04:48,218 --> 01:04:50,052
Did, uh, Nicky come back today?

1315
01:04:50,136 --> 01:04:51,011
No.

1316
01:04:51,096 --> 01:04:51,970
[Pauly] Hey, Joe.

1317
01:04:55,225 --> 01:04:56,892
Joe, we gotta talk. We got problems.

1318
01:04:56,976 --> 01:05:00,396
That two-bit crook you work for
has got problems, starting right now.

1319
01:05:00,480 --> 01:05:02,022
We got a situation here, Joey.

1320
01:05:02,607 --> 01:05:05,734
Get in. Gotta stop by the apartments
on the way downtown.

1321
01:05:07,445 --> 01:05:09,655
Fucking Gus shut me down.

1322
01:05:10,740 --> 01:05:13,409
It's Baci, right?
It's this fucking L Street deal.

1323
01:05:13,493 --> 01:05:16,495
We got worse problems than that, Joe.
Nicky's in trouble.

1324
01:05:16,579 --> 01:05:17,413
What trouble?

1325
01:05:17,497 --> 01:05:19,498
He and Bobby Krausse and that kid Zip,

1326
01:05:19,582 --> 01:05:21,959
they tried to do
Anthony's warehouse last night.

1327
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:23,585
What, is he in jail?

1328
01:05:23,670 --> 01:05:25,963
No, he got away,
but they know he was in on it.

1329
01:05:26,881 --> 01:05:28,382
It doesn't make sense.

1330
01:05:29,092 --> 01:05:30,676
Why would Nicky need to do a robbery?

1331
01:05:30,760 --> 01:05:31,593
[scoffs]

1332
01:05:32,178 --> 01:05:33,929
-Was anybody hurt?
-No, no guns.

1333
01:05:34,013 --> 01:05:35,722
But the thing about it is,

1334
01:05:35,807 --> 01:05:38,016
the DA's office is butting into it.

1335
01:05:38,101 --> 01:05:40,018
The guy's bucking for Senate, right.

1336
01:05:40,103 --> 01:05:42,396
They figure they go after Nicky,
respectable family,

1337
01:05:42,480 --> 01:05:45,983
juice with the people downtown,
shows he's impartial, right?

1338
01:05:46,067 --> 01:05:47,943
Incorruptible, all that shit.

1339
01:05:48,027 --> 01:05:49,695
They're trying to bury him, Joe.

1340
01:05:49,779 --> 01:05:52,614
They got a stolen van,
Anthony's place, no mercy.

1341
01:05:54,284 --> 01:05:56,994
I asked the mayor as a personal favor
to hold them off.

1342
01:05:57,078 --> 01:05:58,162
He's made an effort.

1343
01:05:58,246 --> 01:06:01,206
But l gotta tell you,
I don't think his heart is in it.

1344
01:06:01,291 --> 01:06:04,960
And what would it take
to put his heart back into it?

1345
01:06:05,044 --> 01:06:07,796
What we talked about
with L Street. Tonight.

1346
01:06:12,218 --> 01:06:13,510
This is my kid.

1347
01:06:14,053 --> 01:06:16,388
You're using my kid against me like this?

1348
01:06:16,473 --> 01:06:17,306
Your nephew?

1349
01:06:17,390 --> 01:06:20,642
It's grand larceny, Joe.
And Nicky put us here, not me.

1350
01:06:25,356 --> 01:06:27,566
Look at this place, Joe. It's a dump.

1351
01:06:27,650 --> 01:06:30,194
It wouldn't be
if your outfit didn't have my hands tied.

1352
01:06:30,278 --> 01:06:32,696
It's coming down anyway, sooner or later.

1353
01:06:36,576 --> 01:06:39,244
They're not asking you
to do the thing itself.

1354
01:06:40,205 --> 01:06:44,541
They just need to be sure once it's done,
you don't go fixing the place back up.

1355
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:47,753
Where's Nicky?

1356
01:06:48,880 --> 01:06:52,132
He's okay. They haven't found him yet.
I put the word out, kid gloves.

1357
01:06:53,885 --> 01:06:56,011
I'm gonna have to go to Kerrigan on this.

1358
01:06:58,640 --> 01:07:00,599
What the fuck?

1359
01:07:02,602 --> 01:07:03,435
Yo.

1360
01:07:05,230 --> 01:07:06,063
Gus.

1361
01:07:06,606 --> 01:07:08,524
Hello, Joe, what do you know?

1362
01:07:08,608 --> 01:07:09,525
What's this?

1363
01:07:09,609 --> 01:07:12,736
You got six or seven violations here.
I haven't even been to the basement yet.

1364
01:07:12,820 --> 01:07:13,654
Oh, you.

1365
01:07:14,197 --> 01:07:15,739
You're gonna pay some fines, Joe.

1366
01:07:15,823 --> 01:07:17,115
Oh, you fuck.

1367
01:07:18,785 --> 01:07:21,245
And just yesterday it was all up to code.

1368
01:07:22,163 --> 01:07:24,289
Things fall apart quick, don't they?

1369
01:07:29,087 --> 01:07:31,088
[diners chattering]

1370
01:07:33,466 --> 01:07:35,133
-Hi.
-Hi.

1371
01:07:35,218 --> 01:07:36,301
I'm Nick. I was...

1372
01:07:36,386 --> 01:07:39,054
Yeah, I'll go get her. She's in the annex.

1373
01:07:39,138 --> 01:07:39,972
Thanks.

1374
01:07:41,224 --> 01:07:44,184
Yo, Nicky, you a busboy here or what?

1375
01:07:44,269 --> 01:07:46,603
-[Nick] What are you guys doing out?
-City shut us down.

1376
01:07:46,688 --> 01:07:47,604
[Nick] What for?

1377
01:07:47,689 --> 01:07:49,565
What do you care? You quit.

1378
01:07:49,649 --> 01:07:51,108
Nicky, come over here.

1379
01:07:51,192 --> 01:07:52,401
I wanna talk to you.

1380
01:08:01,411 --> 01:08:05,706
Nicky, the cops come by
just after your old man left the site.

1381
01:08:05,790 --> 01:08:07,874
-You in trouble?
-[sighs]

1382
01:08:07,959 --> 01:08:09,042
I might be.

1383
01:08:09,877 --> 01:08:13,005
-You need a few bills to see you through?
-No, no, no.

1384
01:08:13,089 --> 01:08:15,465
They had a real hard-on for you, Nicky.

1385
01:08:15,550 --> 01:08:18,218
If I were you, I wouldn't go back
to your place for a while.

1386
01:08:19,262 --> 01:08:20,345
Take it light, huh?

1387
01:08:21,681 --> 01:08:22,514
Thanks.

1388
01:08:22,599 --> 01:08:23,724
[Wynn] All l see right now

1389
01:08:23,808 --> 01:08:27,019
is that you and your people are
selling off my district, piece by piece.

1390
01:08:27,103 --> 01:08:28,729
What brings revenue to the city,

1391
01:08:28,813 --> 01:08:31,315
what brings life to the city,
is good for everybody.

1392
01:08:31,399 --> 01:08:33,442
Right, the trickle-down theory.

1393
01:08:33,526 --> 01:08:35,819
But things only seem
to trickle down so far.

1394
01:08:35,903 --> 01:08:38,488
Can't expect the developer to build
if he can't make a profit.

1395
01:08:38,573 --> 01:08:40,949
You don't expect people
to watch their neighborhood be plowed

1396
01:08:41,034 --> 01:08:42,117
without lifting a finger.

1397
01:08:42,201 --> 01:08:43,702
The development creates jobs.

1398
01:08:43,786 --> 01:08:45,954
With jobs, people can afford higher rents.

1399
01:08:46,039 --> 01:08:48,582
And those jobs are gonna go
to the people on L Street?

1400
01:08:48,666 --> 01:08:49,875
Tell me another one.

1401
01:08:50,585 --> 01:08:52,002
[laughs]

1402
01:08:52,086 --> 01:08:54,838
I was hoping that
we could cut some kind of a deal here.

1403
01:08:54,922 --> 01:08:56,340
You mean a personal deal?

1404
01:08:56,424 --> 01:08:59,301
I hear that you got your brother-in-law
on Mad Anthony's payroll.

1405
01:08:59,385 --> 01:09:00,385
What does that mean?

1406
01:09:00,470 --> 01:09:02,304
I understand what it's like.

1407
01:09:02,889 --> 01:09:04,431
New guy on the council.

1408
01:09:04,515 --> 01:09:06,183
The last man at the banquet.

1409
01:09:06,267 --> 01:09:08,185
People expect you to deliver.

1410
01:09:09,228 --> 01:09:11,063
Okay, I got housing inspectors,

1411
01:09:11,147 --> 01:09:12,898
I got teacher's aides.

1412
01:09:12,982 --> 01:09:15,275
You keep pushing Galaxy Towers
the way it's set up now,

1413
01:09:15,360 --> 01:09:17,944
we'll fight you
on blighting classification, on evictions,

1414
01:09:18,029 --> 01:09:22,282
on construction and demolition,
every little step of the way.

1415
01:09:22,367 --> 01:09:24,326
We'll make the L Street apartments
a symbol

1416
01:09:24,410 --> 01:09:27,037
for everything
that's fucked up in this city.

1417
01:09:27,914 --> 01:09:30,290
They can't be a symbol
if they aren't there.

1418
01:09:31,668 --> 01:09:34,503
Sounds like they got you
by the short one, Joey.

1419
01:09:35,755 --> 01:09:36,922
I was wondering, uh,

1420
01:09:37,548 --> 01:09:40,217
since your people fronted me
the money on this thing...

1421
01:09:40,301 --> 01:09:43,303
[laughs]
You want me to get Baci off your back?

1422
01:09:43,388 --> 01:09:46,390
Well, he's hurting your investment.

1423
01:09:46,974 --> 01:09:48,350
We invested in you, Joe.

1424
01:09:48,935 --> 01:09:52,562
This creep,
he's using my family against me.

1425
01:09:53,690 --> 01:09:56,149
You think he didn't check with us
before he made a move?

1426
01:09:58,152 --> 01:10:00,445
And if l blow my bid
on the apartment building?

1427
01:10:00,530 --> 01:10:01,780
If I can't make the payments?

1428
01:10:01,864 --> 01:10:03,490
What would a regular bank do?

1429
01:10:03,574 --> 01:10:08,161
You're not a regular bank.
I'm carrying your people on my payroll.

1430
01:10:11,582 --> 01:10:12,499
Look, Joe.

1431
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:14,710
We appreciate that.

1432
01:10:15,336 --> 01:10:16,294
We really do.

1433
01:10:17,797 --> 01:10:21,049
You'd still get to put up buildings,
you just wouldn't be your own boss.

1434
01:10:22,051 --> 01:10:23,969
Maybe you never were, really.

1435
01:10:25,847 --> 01:10:29,015
I borrowed from you
to get something for myself.

1436
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:33,562
Without Baci, without my brother.

1437
01:10:35,732 --> 01:10:38,233
That's not the way our society works, Joe.

1438
01:10:38,317 --> 01:10:41,778
You got something good, first everybody
on top of you gets a taste,

1439
01:10:42,321 --> 01:10:44,614
then you share what's left
with everybody below you.

1440
01:10:45,491 --> 01:10:48,243
We're social animals,
human beings, not dogs.

1441
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:52,497
Come on, Joe. You'll do what you have to.

1442
01:10:53,541 --> 01:10:56,668
And the people who know,
the people that count,

1443
01:10:57,336 --> 01:10:58,754
they'll understand, Joe.

1444
01:10:59,422 --> 01:11:01,047
They'll respect you for it.

1445
01:11:03,468 --> 01:11:04,301
Thanks.

1446
01:11:20,109 --> 01:11:21,234
Shit.

1447
01:11:21,319 --> 01:11:22,152
[Roger] Les?

1448
01:11:23,488 --> 01:11:24,863
Preparing a lecture?

1449
01:11:25,615 --> 01:11:26,448
Right.

1450
01:11:29,452 --> 01:11:33,955
Listen, we heard about you getting mugged.

1451
01:11:34,832 --> 01:11:36,875
I was really sad to hear that.

1452
01:11:36,959 --> 01:11:38,084
Thanks.

1453
01:11:38,169 --> 01:11:40,295
And we heard the rest,

1454
01:11:40,379 --> 01:11:43,173
the rumor, about the countercharges.

1455
01:11:43,800 --> 01:11:47,219
I wanted to say that we're really glad
you're gonna fight this out.

1456
01:11:47,804 --> 01:11:48,637
Who's "we"?

1457
01:11:51,891 --> 01:11:53,225
"We" us.

1458
01:11:53,309 --> 01:11:56,144
You know, those of us
who are gay on the faculty,

1459
01:11:56,771 --> 01:11:58,021
our friends in the community.

1460
01:11:58,105 --> 01:11:59,856
How could everybody
have heard of it so soon?

1461
01:11:59,941 --> 01:12:03,902
Anyhow, we... l think it's great
that you're taking a stand.

1462
01:12:03,986 --> 01:12:05,654
Who says I'm taking a stand?

1463
