of every heavy hitter in the community.

1497
01:13:30,489 --> 01:13:32,824
The Black press, everyone.
He'll ask that same question.

1498
01:13:32,909 --> 01:13:34,743
How do you think I'd better answer?

1499
01:13:34,827 --> 01:13:36,536
Do you think they were telling the truth?

1500
01:13:36,621 --> 01:13:38,872
Politically speaking, it doesn't matter.

1501
01:13:41,000 --> 01:13:42,334
It matters to me.

1502
01:13:45,296 --> 01:13:48,173
[Angela]
You like that. You like that, don't you?

1503
01:13:48,257 --> 01:13:52,302
Yes, you like that. You like that so much.

1504
01:13:52,386 --> 01:13:55,388
I'm 1 0 years older than my brother was
when he was killed.

1505
01:13:55,473 --> 01:13:57,682
Okay, let's go for a walk, okay?

1506
01:13:57,767 --> 01:13:59,225
He was just a kid.

1507
01:13:59,310 --> 01:14:00,977
My big famous brother.

1508
01:14:03,564 --> 01:14:05,732
-I've been thinking...
-Good boy.

1509
01:14:05,816 --> 01:14:09,027
What have l done with my life
in those last 1 0 years?

1510
01:14:09,111 --> 01:14:12,656
I mean, what have l got
to show for all that time?

1511
01:14:13,699 --> 01:14:15,617
What do you think you should've done?

1512
01:14:16,661 --> 01:14:17,869
I don't know.

1513
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:20,163
Have a family?

1514
01:14:20,247 --> 01:14:23,416
No, not a family.

1515
01:14:23,501 --> 01:14:25,001
Do something heroic?

1516
01:14:25,086 --> 01:14:28,505
Maybe. Not...
You know, not in the Army, though.

1517
01:14:28,589 --> 01:14:31,091
-What is that? What is that?
-Nothing like that.

1518
01:14:31,175 --> 01:14:32,175
Something big.

1519
01:14:33,052 --> 01:14:34,719
I want to be my own boss.

1520
01:14:35,304 --> 01:14:36,680
What, like your father?

1521
01:14:36,764 --> 01:14:37,889
No.

1522
01:14:37,974 --> 01:14:39,057
Not like him.

1523
01:14:39,850 --> 01:14:41,184
Not anything like him.

1524
01:14:42,853 --> 01:14:45,855
[melancholy, pensive music playing]

1525
01:14:54,532 --> 01:14:55,824
[music fades]

1526
01:15:06,127 --> 01:15:07,168
So it's you.

1527
01:15:07,753 --> 01:15:08,712
Yeah.

1528
01:15:08,796 --> 01:15:10,922
I guess l shouldn't be surprised.

1529
01:15:11,007 --> 01:15:14,217
People do favors for me,
I do favors for them.

1530
01:15:15,011 --> 01:15:16,970
You know how it works, Joe.

1531
01:15:17,054 --> 01:15:18,388
Why does it have to be tonight?

1532
01:15:18,472 --> 01:15:20,640
Look, the fire is very minor.

1533
01:15:20,725 --> 01:15:23,810
We gut two or three floors
on the abandoned side,

1534
01:15:23,894 --> 01:15:25,520
other side of the firewall.

1535
01:15:25,604 --> 01:15:26,855
After I get my kid in there,

1536
01:15:26,939 --> 01:15:30,608
make a few adjustments
to the sprinkler system, we get a flood.

1537
01:15:30,693 --> 01:15:31,735
Water damage.

1538
01:15:31,819 --> 01:15:35,030
Nobody gets hurt,
nobody moves back in either.

1539
01:15:35,114 --> 01:15:36,531
I don't like it.

1540
01:15:36,615 --> 01:15:38,742
You're not supposed to like it, Joe.

1541
01:15:38,826 --> 01:15:42,912
You're supposed to bend over,
spread your cheeks, take it like a man.

1542
01:15:43,664 --> 01:15:46,541
Not too fucking thrilled about it myself.

1543
01:15:46,625 --> 01:15:49,627
Don't organize any block parties
down there tonight.

1544
01:15:53,799 --> 01:15:56,760
It's life, Joe. What are you gonna do?

1545
01:16:00,973 --> 01:16:03,975
[melancholy, pensive music resumes]

1546
01:16:06,562 --> 01:16:08,688
You don't have to do this, you know.

1547
01:16:08,773 --> 01:16:10,482
I'm not gonna let them run my life.

1548
01:16:10,566 --> 01:16:12,275
If I back down now, they win.

1549
01:16:13,486 --> 01:16:14,903
Who's keeping score?

1550
01:16:16,739 --> 01:16:18,073
I'll see you in a bit.

1551
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:56,861
I have to be careful when he's got a cold.

1552
01:16:57,530 --> 01:16:59,781
He's always had a hard time breathing.

1553
01:17:06,372 --> 01:17:07,997
Hey, you shaved.

1554
01:17:08,082 --> 01:17:09,833
Yeah, there was a razor in there.

1555
01:17:09,917 --> 01:17:11,042
Ooh.

1556
01:17:11,127 --> 01:17:12,794
I use that for my legs.

1557
01:17:14,171 --> 01:17:16,047
You're lucky you got skin left.

1558
01:17:16,882 --> 01:17:19,676
Yeah, well, l haven't been
to my place all day.

1559
01:17:19,760 --> 01:17:21,469
You break up with your girlfriend?

1560
01:17:21,554 --> 01:17:25,348
Oh, I haven't been with anybody
for a while now.

1561
01:17:25,432 --> 01:17:26,724
Why not?

1562
01:17:26,809 --> 01:17:28,685
Whenever l need somebody,

1563
01:17:28,769 --> 01:17:32,230
it's like, zap,
all the women in the world disappear.

1564
01:17:32,314 --> 01:17:36,234
I swear they smell me coming
from a block away and they hide somewhere.

1565
01:17:36,777 --> 01:17:39,320
It's the same with guys
when they find out I got a kid.

1566
01:17:39,405 --> 01:17:42,907
They figure all l got on my mind
is roping them into getting married.

1567
01:17:45,411 --> 01:17:47,662
Well, what is it you got on your mind?

1568
01:17:48,581 --> 01:17:51,124
Usually something about
how much sleep I can get,

1569
01:17:51,208 --> 01:17:53,668
and still go to school, and go to work,

1570
01:17:53,752 --> 01:17:55,879
and do Jesse's therapy every night.

1571
01:17:57,047 --> 01:17:58,464
It's very romantic.

1572
01:18:01,719 --> 01:18:03,428
I guess you can get used to anything.

1573
01:18:04,013 --> 01:18:06,347
I don't wanna get used to it. It sucks.

1574
01:18:26,535 --> 01:18:29,162
You, uh-- You can't be a creep, okay?

1575
01:18:29,246 --> 01:18:32,874
I mean, you start any bullshit,
I just don't have the energy.

1576
01:18:32,958 --> 01:18:34,334
I'll do my best.

1577
01:18:35,294 --> 01:18:36,961
I'm kind of defensive, huh?

1578
01:18:37,630 --> 01:18:40,548
You're like a surgeon general's warning
with legs.

1579
01:18:40,633 --> 01:18:41,633
I'm sorry.

1580
01:18:42,468 --> 01:18:43,801
I mean it though, huh?

1581
01:18:45,221 --> 01:18:46,471
Don't worry about it.

1582
01:19:24,343 --> 01:19:25,677
Do you have anything?

1583
01:19:26,220 --> 01:19:27,595
Aren't you on anything?

1584
01:19:28,555 --> 01:19:30,056
No, I have something.

1585
01:19:31,225 --> 01:19:32,976
You got quite a supply there.

1586
01:19:33,519 --> 01:19:35,270
A girl can dream, can't she?

1587
01:19:35,354 --> 01:19:36,354
You want?

1588
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,356
Yeah, when we get to that point.

1589
01:19:45,406 --> 01:19:47,407
[Jesse coughing]

1590
01:19:47,491 --> 01:19:48,324
Wait.

1591
01:19:48,409 --> 01:19:49,242
What?

1592
01:19:51,620 --> 01:19:52,453
What is it?

1593
01:19:58,377 --> 01:19:59,294
It's all right.

1594
01:20:03,048 --> 01:20:04,382
You still up for this?

1595
01:20:05,968 --> 01:20:07,218
