01:27:36,209 --> 01:27:39,712
Look... Hey, Levonne.
Levonne, you working here?

1716
01:27:39,796 --> 01:27:42,339
No, I just came by to check out the show.

1717
01:27:42,424 --> 01:27:45,009
I ain't seen so much paper in all my life.

1718
01:27:45,093 --> 01:27:47,094
All of them ask the same damn questions.

1719
01:27:47,179 --> 01:27:50,222
You see, it helps them
to stall while they try to figure out...

1720
01:27:50,307 --> 01:27:52,933
Why settle for less
when you can have it all?

1721
01:27:53,018 --> 01:27:55,478
Why settle for less
when you can have it all?

1722
01:27:56,021 --> 01:27:59,482
Money talks, nobody walks.
Money talks, nobody walks.

1723
01:27:59,566 --> 01:28:01,233
Money talks, nobody walks...

1724
01:28:02,152 --> 01:28:04,153
[speaking in Spanish]

1725
01:28:08,658 --> 01:28:09,825
-[in English] Hi, Wynn.
-Uh...

1726
01:28:09,910 --> 01:28:11,994
Hi. How many people was it?

1727
01:28:12,078 --> 01:28:15,873
Uh, 1 3 families, a couple of singles.

1728
01:28:15,957 --> 01:28:18,083
Only a few have family they can stay with.

1729
01:28:18,168 --> 01:28:21,086
How long till they rehab the side
that didn't burn?

1730
01:28:21,171 --> 01:28:22,880
Rinaldi says it's totaled.

1731
01:28:22,964 --> 01:28:25,549
He's gonna knock it down
and sell the land.

1732
01:28:26,593 --> 01:28:28,052
The development package.

1733
01:28:29,638 --> 01:28:31,055
Not very subtle, are they?

1734
01:28:31,139 --> 01:28:32,223
[speaks in Spanish]

1735
01:28:33,767 --> 01:28:35,309
-[in English] I'll see you later.
-Yeah.

1736
01:28:36,853 --> 01:28:37,686
Levonne.

1737
01:28:38,647 --> 01:28:40,272
What's this, Wynn?

1738
01:28:40,357 --> 01:28:41,440
Photo opportunity?

1739
01:28:41,525 --> 01:28:43,484
And what would you be saying
if l didn't come?

1740
01:28:44,569 --> 01:28:45,778
-Hi.
-Hi.

1741
01:28:45,862 --> 01:28:46,987
Whose is this?

1742
01:28:47,072 --> 01:28:48,906
-Mine. Hold her for a minute?
-Yeah?

1743
01:28:48,990 --> 01:28:51,075
-Yeah. Felice had to work today.
-Hey, there.

1744
01:28:51,159 --> 01:28:52,201
What's your name?

1745
01:28:52,994 --> 01:28:54,453
[laughs] She looks just like you.

1746
01:28:54,538 --> 01:28:55,621
Yeah, maybe.

1747
01:28:56,164 --> 01:28:59,083
Can l talk to you?
I wish you'd reconsider this meeting.

1748
01:28:59,167 --> 01:29:01,502
If you have to kiss the man's ass,
that's your problem.

1749
01:29:01,586 --> 01:29:04,922
That's off the point. This here,
this is what's worth fighting for.

1750
01:29:05,006 --> 01:29:07,550
-We have to choose where we make a stand.
-What "we"?

1751
01:29:07,634 --> 01:29:09,301
Okay, it's your ass.

1752
01:29:20,313 --> 01:29:21,856
They probably started it themselves.

1753
01:29:22,732 --> 01:29:24,358
They had no power in there.

1754
01:29:24,901 --> 01:29:28,404
They used candles and shit.
Probably knocked something over.

1755
01:29:28,989 --> 01:29:30,030
Arson.

1756
01:29:30,115 --> 01:29:31,115
Huh?

1757
01:29:31,199 --> 01:29:33,742
Arson. It was a torch job. Professional.

1758
01:29:36,663 --> 01:29:37,913
How do you know that?

1759
01:29:37,998 --> 01:29:40,499
Because l lived here 40 years, that's how.

1760
01:29:40,584 --> 01:29:43,752
Listen to me, I want you
to be calm about this, all right?

1761
01:29:43,837 --> 01:29:46,213
The guy you went off on yesterday
made the charts.

1762
01:29:46,298 --> 01:29:47,506
Nick Rinaldi?

1763
01:29:48,550 --> 01:29:49,842
What'd he do?

1764
01:29:49,926 --> 01:29:51,051
Robbery suspect.

1765
01:29:51,595 --> 01:29:52,970
Suspect, right?

1766
01:29:53,054 --> 01:29:55,723
No guns involved. No priors.

1767
01:29:55,807 --> 01:29:58,434
No reason to believe
he's armed or dangerous.

1768
01:29:58,518 --> 01:30:01,020
We see him, you stay in the car,
I make the collar, right?

1769
01:30:02,314 --> 01:30:03,439
-Right?
-Right.

1770
01:30:03,523 --> 01:30:05,941
Just let me at him in the fucking car.

1771
01:30:06,026 --> 01:30:07,151
You're a mess, kid.

1772
01:30:09,613 --> 01:30:10,446
Where you turning?

1773
01:30:11,197 --> 01:30:13,866
The site up here. He was working that job.

1774
01:30:13,950 --> 01:30:16,118
Ferraro checked it out yesterday. He quit.

1775
01:30:16,661 --> 01:30:18,329
Fucking deadbeat.

1776
01:30:18,413 --> 01:30:21,332
She takes up
with a fucking deadbeat thief.

1777
01:30:21,416 --> 01:30:22,750
What's it to you anymore?

1778
01:30:22,834 --> 01:30:25,085
Hey, Tom, it reflects on me, all right?

1779
01:30:25,170 --> 01:30:27,671
She's my ex-wife, the mother of my child.

1780
01:30:27,756 --> 01:30:28,756
Child?

1781
01:30:29,466 --> 01:30:31,383
You never told me you had a kid.

1782
01:30:32,135 --> 01:30:33,302
Boy or girl?

1783
01:30:33,887 --> 01:30:34,970
Boy.

1784
01:30:35,055 --> 01:30:36,388
How old?

1785
01:30:38,558 --> 01:30:39,391
He's 2.

1786
01:30:40,518 --> 01:30:42,353
Huh. Two-year-old son, huh?

1787
01:30:43,772 --> 01:30:45,230
I never knew you had a kid.

1788
01:30:47,817 --> 01:30:48,817
Well, I do.

1789
01:30:54,282 --> 01:30:56,283
[man speaking indistinctly]

1790
01:30:57,744 --> 01:31:01,914
If you like that one, I'll be glad
to make the estimate for you.

1791
01:31:05,710 --> 01:31:06,543
Hector.

1792
01:31:08,088 --> 01:31:10,798
Whatever she wants,
you cut your price in half.

1793
01:31:11,341 --> 01:31:12,758
I'll pay the difference.

1794
01:31:13,927 --> 01:31:15,302
And don't let her know.

1795
01:31:20,100 --> 01:31:22,017
-[man 1] Hey, Errol.
-[man 2] Hey, Errol.

1796
01:31:22,102 --> 01:31:23,477
Morning, fellas.

1797
01:31:24,688 --> 01:31:27,314
It was a lot more fun playing here
when they were afraid of me.

1798
01:31:27,399 --> 01:31:29,733
-I took them to court.
-This was restricted?

1799
01:31:29,818 --> 01:31:32,903
Yeah, no Blacks, no Jews,
no undesirable elements.

1800
01:31:32,988 --> 01:31:36,740
I'd hang out at the 1 8th green
by the clubhouse, and just smile,

1801
01:31:36,825 --> 01:31:39,660
and make the old bastards
1 2-putt the final hole.

1802
01:31:39,744 --> 01:31:41,996
Took two years before anybody said hello.

1803
01:31:42,080 --> 01:31:44,498
Must've been tough
to concentrate on your game.

1804
01:31:45,250 --> 01:31:46,583
I never played better.

1805
01:31:52,298 --> 01:31:54,800
So you've got yourself
a nice little mess, Wynn.

1806
01:31:55,343 --> 01:31:56,844
Makes me glad I'm retired.

1807
01:31:56,928 --> 01:31:58,637
You were operating on a bigger scale.

1808
01:31:58,722 --> 01:32:00,055
Scale doesn't matter.

1809
01:32:00,140 --> 01:32:02,099
You always try to gain some ground,

1810
01:32:02,183 --> 01:32:05,227
no matter what the situation is,
and make some good come out of it.

1811
01:32:05,311 --> 01:32:07,396
I don't see how this is good for anybody.

1812
01:32:07,480 --> 01:32:09,148
You think those boys are lying, don't you?

1813
01:32:09,232 --> 01:32:11,442
-Well...
-You wouldn't be here otherwise.

1814
01:32:11,526 --> 01:32:14,403
I think it's too big
for them to go back on their story now.

1815
01:32:15,488 --> 01:32:17,489
[laughs]

1816
01:32:19,868 --> 01:32:21,577
I didn't use enough club.

1817
01:32:22,412 --> 01:32:26,040
I hate it when I do that.
I nibble my way up to the green.

1818
01:32:26,124 --> 01:32:27,332
It's a failure of nerve.

1819
01:32:27,417 --> 01:32:29,293
Why l have to take a stance
on this at all...

1820
01:32:29,377 --> 01:32:31,128
-You're not a policeman.
-Right.

1821
01:32:31,212 --> 01:32:32,504
-Nor a judge.
-Right.

1822
01:32:32,589 --> 01:32:33,422
Right.

1823
01:32:34,340 --> 01:32:36,633
But the moment will come
when Levonne will put it to me

1824
01:32:36,718 --> 01:32:39,887
in front of the whole community,
"Do you think our boys are lying?"

1825
01:32:41,097 --> 01:32:41,930
Wedge?

1826
01:32:42,891 --> 01:32:44,475
[sighs] What?

1827
01:32:44,559 --> 01:32:47,352
Do you think l could use a wedge
from this far out?

1828
01:32:47,854 --> 01:32:49,396
[sighs] l don't play.

1829
01:32:49,939 --> 01:32:52,274
-Tennis? Racquetball?
-I don't play anything.

1830
01:32:54,235 --> 01:32:55,569
You do have a problem.

1831
01:32:58,364 --> 01:32:59,198
You, um...

1832
01:33:01,076 --> 01:33:02,910
You could say you believe them.

1833
01:33:02,994 --> 01:33:06,455
If we're gonna take power,
we have to take responsibility too.

1834
01:33:07,290 --> 01:33:09,291
You're absolutely right, professor.

1835
01:33:10,668 --> 01:33:12,294
How are you, darling?

1836
01:33:12,378 --> 01:33:14,922
It's good to see you up and around again.

1837
01:33:15,006 --> 01:33:17,674
You got your color back. That's marvelous.

1838
01:33:17,759 --> 01:33:20,719
Oh, you should've been there last night.
We had a big one.

1839
01:33:20,804 --> 01:33:22,763
The equipment our boys have now.

1840
01:33:22,847 --> 01:33:24,932
Not like in your day,
a bucket and a ladder.

1841
01:33:25,016 --> 01:33:26,809
How's your fingers, huh? Make a fist.

1842
01:33:26,893 --> 01:33:28,227
Beautiful, beautiful.

1843
01:33:28,895 --> 01:33:31,897
Did you come for the lasagna, Joe,
or is this official business?

1844
01:33:31,981 --> 01:33:33,774
Two people are dead because of you and me.

1845
01:33:33,858 --> 01:33:36,985
They were trespassing. Those are the kind
of people accidents happen to.

1846
01:33:37,779 --> 01:33:38,946
You suck.

1847
01:33:39,030 --> 01:33:41,907
Joe, things change fast.

1848
01:33:41,991 --> 01:33:44,910
People get hurt. I'm sorry about that.

1849
01:33:44,994 --> 01:33:46,495
It was an accident.

1850
01:33:46,579 --> 01:33:48,122
Now if everybody stands up

1851
01:33:48,206 --> 01:33:51,041
like a good soldier,
we can stay on top of it.

1852
01:33:51,126 --> 01:33:54,253
Joe, in the next couple of years,

1853
01:33:54,337 --> 01:33:57,297
this town is gonna be one big yard sale.

1854
01:33:57,382 --> 01:34:00,634
And anyone with a half a brain
will make tracks,

1855
01:34:00,718 --> 01:34:05,013
let the Blacks and the Spanish
duke it out over whatever's left.

1856
01:34:05,598 --> 01:34:07,766
I want you off of my kid.

1857
01:34:07,851 --> 01:34:11,186
I'll call Walsh.
We'll take his name out of the computer.

1858
01:34:11,271 --> 01:34:12,396
It never happened.

1859
01:34:12,480 --> 01:34:13,313
And the other two?

1860
01:34:14,107 --> 01:34:17,526
Anthony is good people.
He'll drop the charges if l tell him to.

1861
01:34:18,486 --> 01:34:19,570
Tell him to.

1862
01:34:19,654 --> 01:34:21,613
[all] Surprise.

1863
01:34:24,534 --> 01:34:27,411
Mrs. Donnelly, 90 years old.

1864
01:34:28,163 --> 01:34:32,082
Joe, 90 years ago,
the Irish ran this town.

1865
01:34:32,167 --> 01:34:34,751
There were horses shitting
on Jefferson Street.

1866
01:34:34,836 --> 01:34:38,172
My grandfather got here off the boat.

1867
01:34:38,256 --> 01:34:40,465
They gave him a scoop and a shovel.

1868
01:34:40,550 --> 01:34:42,509
Now l run the place.

1869
01:34:43,511 --> 01:34:44,761
America, huh?

1870
01:34:47,807 --> 01:34:52,686
♪ America, America ♪

1871
01:34:52,770 --> 01:34:57,399
♪ God shed his grace on thee ♪

1872
01:34:57,984 --> 01:35:00,736
♪ And crown thy good ♪

1873
01:35:00,820 --> 01:35:03,614
♪ With brotherhood ♪

1874
01:35:03,698 --> 01:35:07,868
♪ From sea to shining sea ♪

1875
01:35:08,578 --> 01:35:10,329
-Let's try it one more time.
-[knocks on door]

1876
01:35:12,582 --> 01:35:14,124
I'm gonna step out for a second.

1877
01:35:14,209 --> 01:35:17,377
If I'm not back,
do The Star-Spangled Banner, okay??

1878
01:35:18,922 --> 01:35:21,048
I wanna be able
to hear your voice, Warren.

1879
01:35:23,885 --> 01:35:25,510
Where the hell have you been?

1880
01:35:25,595 --> 01:35:28,096
I've been calling your apartment.
There were police.

1881
01:35:28,181 --> 01:35:30,098
-They came here?
-Oh, yeah. Big show.

1882
01:35:30,183 --> 01:35:32,142
Kids treated me like a TV star.

1883
01:35:32,227 --> 01:35:33,518
I got some problems.

1884
01:35:33,603 --> 01:35:36,188
Being late with the rent
is having some problems, Nick.

1885
01:35:36,272 --> 01:35:39,524
Cops after you for robbery
is being seriously fucked up.

1886
01:35:39,609 --> 01:35:41,026
-Listen.
-No, you listen.

1887
01:35:41,110 --> 01:35:43,028
You know where Mom was this morning?

1888
01:35:43,112 --> 01:35:44,988
In church, praying for you.

1889
01:35:45,740 --> 01:35:48,408
You turn her into a religious fanatic,
Nicky, so help me...

1890
01:35:48,493 --> 01:35:51,203
Laurie, l need you to do something for me.

1891
01:35:51,788 --> 01:35:53,330
We had a deal.

1892
01:35:54,249 --> 01:35:55,374
You remember?

1893
01:35:55,458 --> 01:35:58,752
After Tony died?
You and me against the world.

1894
01:36:01,506 --> 01:36:04,841
How come I'm always helping you out
and I never get anything back?

1895
01:36:04,926 --> 01:36:07,135
I helped you with that marriage deal.

1896
01:36:07,220 --> 01:36:08,845
You fucked up my engagement.

1897
01:36:08,930 --> 01:36:09,763
He was an asshole.

1898
01:36:09,847 --> 01:36:11,223
He was my asshole.

1899
01:36:11,307 --> 01:36:13,100
Hey, listen, listen, listen.

1900
01:36:13,184 --> 01:36:15,352
I'm gonna turn myself in, okay?

1901
01:36:15,436 --> 01:36:18,146
I just need
to straighten some things out first.

1902
01:36:18,690 --> 01:36:20,649
I think Dad might be in trouble.

1903
01:36:21,943 --> 01:36:24,903
Yeah, one of his apartment buildings
burned down last night.

1904
01:36:24,988 --> 01:36:27,155
People were killed.
Yeah, I'd say he's got trouble.

1905
01:36:27,240 --> 01:36:30,450
I think it might be worse than that,
all right?

1906
01:36:31,452 --> 01:36:32,286
Now...

1907
01:36:33,496 --> 01:36:35,497
Now call him up, be nice to him.

1908
01:36:35,581 --> 01:36:38,083
You know, I don't know, talk or something.

1909
01:36:38,167 --> 01:36:39,876
-Why can't you do that?
-I can't.

1910
01:36:39,961 --> 01:36:40,794
Why not?

1911
01:36:42,463 --> 01:36:43,797
I can't.

1912
01:36:47,719 --> 01:36:49,678
Doesn't work that way between us.

1913
01:36:50,722 --> 01:36:52,431
Please, don't get hurt, Nick.

1914
01:36:54,392 --> 01:36:57,394
I was one of the first Black mayors
of a major city in this county.

1915
01:36:57,937 --> 01:37:01,732
Lot of media pressure, millions of people
affected by my decisions.

1916
01:37:01,816 --> 01:37:05,444
But there was no way l could turn my back
on the people who put me in.

1917
01:37:05,528 --> 01:37:07,904
So I brought some of them along with me.

1918
01:37:09,157 --> 01:37:10,532
Some of them messed up.

1919
01:37:11,993 --> 01:37:14,411
Well, they're only people. They're human.

1920
01:37:15,413 --> 01:37:17,664
I let it go at first
because l didn't believe it,

1921
01:37:17,749 --> 01:37:20,625
and then because
I didn't want to believe it,

1922
01:37:20,710 --> 01:37:23,712
and finally because
we would lose more ground

1923
01:37:23,796 --> 01:37:25,589
by cleaning house in public

1924
01:37:25,673 --> 01:37:27,758
than by sweeping it under the carpet.

1925
01:37:28,301 --> 01:37:30,802
Took 1 2 years
for all that to catch up to me.

1926
01:37:31,346 --> 01:37:33,889
That's a pretty nice run,
the way things go these days.

1927
01:37:34,432 --> 01:37:36,558
You decided not to run again?

1928
01:37:36,642 --> 01:37:39,561
There were three grand jury indictments
hanging over my head.

1929
01:37:40,104 --> 01:37:42,939
If I'd stood for another term,
a lot of people would've gone down,

1930
01:37:43,024 --> 01:37:44,733
and I would've gone down with them.

1931
01:37:45,443 --> 01:37:48,487
So I should lie,
and hope for 1 2 good years?

1932
01:37:48,571 --> 01:37:50,364
This isn't the Old Testament, Wynn.

1933
01:37:50,448 --> 01:37:53,867
People didn't vote you in
so you can test your moral fiber.

1934
01:37:53,951 --> 01:37:56,161
If you're going to be a leader, lead.

1935
01:37:56,913 --> 01:37:59,081
Take it to the man every chance you get.

1936
01:37:59,165 --> 01:38:03,085
-It's not about a fight with white people.
-It's always about that, Wynn.

1937
01:38:03,836 --> 01:38:06,088
If it isn't,
you're just another ward heeler.

1938
01:38:06,631 --> 01:38:08,173
You don't defend anything.

1939
01:38:08,841 --> 01:38:10,384
You attack what's wrong.

1940
01:38:11,260 --> 01:38:12,803
That's what a leader is.

1941
01:38:20,186 --> 01:38:23,188
I worked so hard to get on the council,
I never thought about...

1942
01:38:23,272 --> 01:38:26,608
Can't know how you'll play the green
while you're still back at the tee, Wynn.

1943
01:38:27,151 --> 01:38:29,653
You just figure it out when you get there.

1944
01:38:36,452 --> 01:38:37,369
[Riggs] Hey, Nick?

1945
01:38:43,000 --> 01:38:44,543
Figured you might be here.

1946
01:38:45,461 --> 01:38:47,963
This was always your favorite hiding spot.

1947
01:38:49,215 --> 01:38:50,215
What do you want?

1948
01:38:52,385 --> 01:38:53,927
To see if you needed help.

1949
01:38:57,598 --> 01:38:59,266
What do you wanna help me for?

1950
01:39:02,395 --> 01:39:05,897
Your brother must have saved my ass
a half-dozen times over there.

1951
01:39:05,982 --> 01:39:07,232
And then your father.

1952
01:39:08,901 --> 01:39:11,236
When I got back, l was pretty messed up.
This job has been...

1953
01:39:11,320 --> 01:39:13,822
-Look, you don't owe me nothing.
-All right.

1954
01:39:15,867 --> 01:39:17,284
The offer stands though.

1955
01:39:18,619 --> 01:39:19,744
You need money?

1956
01:39:20,788 --> 01:39:21,997
A go-between?

1957
01:39:23,332 --> 01:39:26,126
-After your friends thrown you in...
-Who said that?

1958
01:39:27,170 --> 01:39:29,796
The guard saw me.
What are you talking about?

1959
01:39:31,090 --> 01:39:33,550
